{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "name": "CMS Domain API",
    "description": "Postman Collection for the CMS Domain (Feature 021) of the thedevkitchen Real Estate Management System.\n\n## Module\n`thedevkitchen_cms` — Content Management System for real estate agencies.\n\n## Features\n- CMS Pages: Create, list, get, update, delete, and duplicate pages\n- CMS Media: Upload, list, get metadata, download file, and delete media assets\n- CMS Public: Public page rendering endpoint (no session/company required)\n- CMS Templates: Create, list, get, update, and delete reusable page templates\n- CMS Settings: Read and update CMS configuration per company\n\n## Authentication Flow\n1. **Get OAuth Token**: POST /api/v1/auth/token → saves `access_token` + `refresh_token`\n2. **User Login**: POST /api/v1/users/login → saves `session_id`\n3. **Set context variables**: `company_id` from your tenant configuration\n4. **Use triple auth on all CMS endpoints**: `Authorization` + `X-Session-Id` + `X-Company-Id`\n\n## Headers (Authenticated Endpoints)\n- `Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}` — JWT bearer token (@require_jwt)\n- `X-Session-Id: {{session_id}}` — Application session (@require_session)\n- `X-Company-Id: {{company_id}}` — Tenant isolation (@require_company)\n- `User-Agent: {{user_agent}}` — Session fingerprint validation\n- `Content-Type: application/json` — For POST/PUT JSON endpoints\n\n## Headers (Public Endpoint)\n- `Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}` — JWT only (no session/company)\n- `User-Agent: {{user_agent}}`\n\n## Headers (Media Upload)\n- `Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}`\n- `X-Session-Id: {{session_id}}`\n- `X-Company-Id: {{company_id}}`\n- `User-Agent: {{user_agent}}`\n- **No Content-Type** — Postman sets it automatically with multipart boundary\n\n## Important Notes (ADR-016)\n- ⚠️ **No JSON-RPC**: All CMS endpoints send JSON directly in body (no wrapper)\n- ✅ **Variables**: Use {{...}} for all auth values — never hardcode\n- ✅ **Test Scripts**: Create Page/Template/Media auto-save IDs to variables\n- ✅ **Multi-tenancy**: All non-public endpoints enforce company isolation\n\n## Changelog v1.0\n- **NEW**: Initial CMS Domain collection (Feature 021)\n- POST /api/v1/cms/pages — Create Page\n- GET /api/v1/cms/pages — List Pages\n- GET /api/v1/cms/pages/{id} — Get Page\n- PUT /api/v1/cms/pages/{id} — Update Page\n- DELETE /api/v1/cms/pages/{id} — Delete Page\n- POST /api/v1/cms/pages/{id}/duplicate — Duplicate Page\n- POST /api/v1/cms/media/upload — Upload Media\n- GET /api/v1/cms/media — List Media\n- GET /api/v1/cms/media/{id} — Get Media Metadata\n- GET /api/v1/cms/media/{id}/file — Get Media File (binary)\n- DELETE /api/v1/cms/media/{id} — Delete Media\n- GET /api/v1/public/cms/{company_slug}/pages/{page_slug} — Get Public Page\n- POST /api/v1/cms/templates — Create Template\n- GET /api/v1/cms/templates — List Templates\n- GET /api/v1/cms/templates/{id} — Get Template\n- PUT /api/v1/cms/templates/{id} — Update Template\n- DELETE /api/v1/cms/templates/{id} — Delete Template\n- GET /api/v1/cms/settings — Get Settings\n- PUT /api/v1/cms/settings — Update Settings",
    "version": "1.0",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
